Difference between Smoke, Regression and Sanity Test

Smoke Test
Performed on initial or unstable build
Verify basic and critical component
Cover end to end functionality
Employed by both Developers and Testers
Subset of Acceptance testing
Done when there’s new build

Sanity Test
Performed on stable build
Verify added functionality or code change or bug fixes
Cover certain functionality
Carried out by Testers
Subset of Regression Testing
Only carried out in short times

Regression Test
Performed on stable build
Verify all system affected by new code change
Extensively check  mostly all the functionality.
Carried out Testers
Superset of Regression Testing
Usually performed after each update.
